**27-9-2025  Saturday**
**Day 1. Docker Practice**


1. Check if Docker is installed and its version.
2. Run a simple Docker container (hello-world).
3. List all running and stopped containers.
4. List all Docker images on your system.
5. Pull an image from Docker Hub (e.g., Ubuntu).
6. Run an interactive container with bash shell.
7. Exit the container without stopping it.
8. Stop a running container.
9. Remove a stopped container.
10. Remove a Docker image.



***Solution***

1. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker --version
    Docker version 28.4.0, build d8eb465
2. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker run hello-world
3. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker ps -a
4. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker images
5. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker pull ubuntu
6. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker run -it ubuntu bash
7. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker rm ubuntu
8. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> CTRL +P+Q
9. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker stop ubuntu(fervent\_bardeen)
10. PS C:\\Users\\TANISHA> docker rmi ubuntu / docker rmi -f ubuntu